column1: Interactions must be numbered to group interactors.
column2: Reference database for the interactors UniProt
column6: NCBI taxid for the Host Organism in which the interaction took place. Details of tissue or cell lines additional columns
column7: Primary accession number from the referenced database.
column8: Name used for the interactor in the publication as alias, Xrefs provided in publication as aditional columns
column10: The role of the interactor in the interaction, usually bait, prey or neutral component. As experimental role
column16: The biological role of the interactor in the interaction, for example enzyme, enzyme target, cofactor, unspecified role.
column22: Interaction detection method. See Controlled vocabularies
column28: Participant detection method. See for a list of possible methods. Optional.
column40: Other information, e.g. interacting domains, or protein tags. Features
column63: Others - xrefs on alias or on features
